  "text": "All mice were backcrossed onto the C57BL/6 background for a minimum of 6 generations. Wild-type C57BL/6 (DTR Ϫ ), CD11c-DTR (DTR ϩ ), and Ldlr Ϫ/Ϫ mice were from The Jackson Laboratory. DTR ϩ mice were maintained in the hemizygous state, and progeny were genotyped as described. [CITATION_1] The CD11c-DTR transgene was bred onto the Ldlr Ϫ/Ϫ background. DTR ϩ and DTR Ϫ or DTR ϩ Ldlr Ϫ/Ϫ and DTR Ϫ Ldlr Ϫ/Ϫ littermates were used in experiments. Mice were bred and housed under pathogen-free conditions at the University Health Network animal facility. All experiments were performed according to institutional guidelines, as well as Canadian federal and provincial laws for animal protection.",
